IMPORT fs

TYPE Cursor
  pos AS Integer
END TYPE

' plan-59-C: a BARE `RES` parameter's STATE is OPAQUE — §15.5's parameter row
' accepts "any state or none" — so it may not be narrowed to a concrete STATE on
' the way out. This is the `launder` shape: the checker knows only that `f`
' carries *some* state, so declaring a `STATE Cursor` return is a claim it cannot
' discharge (TYPE_STATE_OPAQUE_NARROWING).
'
' Note this is NOT type confusion — it is an unprovable narrowing, the same shape
' as any other. It needs no runtime support, which is why STATE stays entirely
' compile-time checked.
'
' Distinct from resource-state-bare-return-invalid, which is the MIRROR case: a
' bare RETURN of a value that provably carries a state. Here the return names a
' state and the value's is unknown.
FUNC launder(RES f AS File) AS RES File STATE Cursor
  RETURN f
END FUNC

FUNC main AS Integer
  RES h AS File = fs::openFile("tests/syntax/resources/state-opaque-narrow-return-invalid/src/main.mfb")
  fs::close(h)
  RETURN 0
END FUNC
